raden haji harsoyo a retired general 
major and former commander of the indonesian contingent of un 
peacekeeping forces in the vietnam war died tuesday of heart 
disease at age 63 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
william j mcdonald a nationally noted 
cleric who served as auxiliary bishop of the san francisco 
archdiocese for 12 years died saturday of a heart attack at age 83 
mcdonald was ordained in san francisco in 1928 serving as a 
parish priest before going into education he took a doctorate from 
the catholic university of america in washington remaining as a 
faculty member 
mcdonald was president of the international federation of 
catholic universities from 1960 to 1963 and editor of the catholic 
encyclopedia he served as auxiliary bishop in the washington dc 
archdiocese from 1964 to 1967 when he was transferred to san 
francisco 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
karl geiringer an internationally 
known author of books on composers such as johann sebastian bach and 
franz joseph hadyn died tuesday he was 89 
geiringer studied with guido adler one of the fathers of modern 
musicology at the university of vienna there he received his 
doctorate and later became curator of the archives of the society of 
the friends of music which house major collections of the 
manuscripts of composers johannes haydn and robert alexander 
schumann 
geiringer who came to the united states in 1939 wrote more than 
100 articles for groves dictionary of music and musicians he also 
worked for the british broadcasting company and organized the 
collection of instruments owned by the royal college of music 
geiringer who was named professor emeritus at university of 
california santa barbara in 1973 also authored instruments in the 
history of western music composers and musicians throughout the 
world used his books which were translated into 11 languages 
</TEXT>
