the nuclear power plant in an earthquakeprone area 
of soviet armenia will be closed by march soviet television 
reported 
the vremya evening news program reported tuesday night that one 
of the plants reactors would shut down by feb 25 the second by 
march 18 
the plant located in the armenian capital of yerevan was not 
damaged by the devastating dec 7 earthquake in another part of the 
small southern soviet republic that borders turkey 
but officials began to take environmentalists concern over the 
plants hazardous location more seriously after that quake which 
killed at least 25000 people 
premier nikolai ryzhkov said in december that the plant would 
close within two years due to the earthquake danger 
