<TEXT>
the population of seoul totaled 1028 
million people last year making the south korean capital the 
sixthlargest city in the world according to a census released 
today 
the census conducted by the city government in november showed 
the number of people in the capital increased 295 percent from 1987 
and accounted for onefourth of the nations total population 
the number of foreigners residing in seoul fell by 4 percent to 
10195 people the census showed 
foreigners residing in seoul included 3370 americans 3233 
chinese 1513 japanese and 179 west germans according to the 
survey 
the census did not cover the 42000 us troops stationed in the 
city under a defense treaty officials said 
