<TEXT>
the arrest of the head of mexicos powerful 
oil workers union on armssmuggling charges amounts to the opening 
salvo in a political war mounted by newly inaugurated president 
carlos salinas de gortari 
joaquin hernandez galicia known as la quina is a wealthy man 
with enormous political influence who has dispensed patronage to his 
faithful and commanded the loyalty of hundreds of thousands of oil 
workers 
within hours of his arrest thousands of workers walked off the 
job and troops were guarding installations of the stateowned pemex 
oil monopoly 
critics term hernandez galicia 66 the jimmy hoffa of mexico 
admirers see the former welder as a beloved padrino who hands 
out jobs and favors attending to the welfare of his subjects and 
guaranteeing the election of state legislators mayors and city 
councilmen 
challenging la quina is a bold move for salinas who took office 
dec 1 and provides a quick test of his vow to modernize the 
nations political and economic system 
la quina is a classic product of the system that suddenly turned 
on him tuesday when soldiers shot their way into his fortresslike 
home in ciudad madero and arrested him on gunrunning charges a 
federal agent was killed in the raid 
the bad blood between salinas and the union goes back several 
years when salinas was budget director under his predecessor 
miguel de la madrid and pushed through economic reforms that cut 
into the unions concessions 
like other labor bosses who felt threatened by salinas talk of 
reform la quina made no secret of his unhappiness when de la madrid 
chose salinas as his successor the union gave salinas only lukewarm 
support during one of the most hotly contested presidential races in 
mexican history 
a source close to the new president said salinas and his people 
suspect la quina had covertly financed opposition candidate 
cuauhtemoc cardenas 
the rift between the salinas camp and the union widened after the 
election when the union accused a top official of the governing 
institutional revolutionary party gov ramon beteta of mexico 
state of committing fraud in his previous post as pemexs head 
salinas is going to have to put some union leaders in jail 
political analyst adolfo aguilar predicted in an interview shortly 
before salinas took office 
la quinas power stems from its symbiotic relationship between 
the unions and the party that has governed mexico for 60 years it 
is a relationship in which power and profit are exchanged for votes 
and peace in the workplace 
salinas is not the first president to threaten to clean up the 
unions de la madrid had made moral renovation the centerpiece 
of his campaign 
destroying la quina is a necessary step in the moral 
renovation political analyst lorenzo meyer said five years ago 
but la quina survived heading an empire that possessed lucrative 
oil drilling contracts and construction companies to funeral 
parlors ranches and union stores 
although he gave up the post of union secretary general more than 
20 years ago la quina still is de facto leader of a union often 
accused of murder extortion and fraud that doesnt matter to his 
supporters 
the people here love him a lot he is like their father said 
a veteran journalist in tampico which adjoins la quinas home turf 
in ciudad madero on the coast of the gulf of mexico 
in more than 30 years of union politics la quina turned the oil 
workers union into a political and financial powerhouse 
the union won sweeping concessions from pemex in exchange for 
peace and political support for the institutional revolutionary 
party or pri 
among those concessions was the right to handle half the outside 
drilling contracts and the right to dole out jobs with pemex 
hundreds of millions of dollars have flowed legally through the 
union as a result and critics say the union has also amassed a 
fortune under the table 
</TEXT>
