<TEXT>
the supreme court overturned a military censors 
ruling and allowed publication of a news story criticizing the 
director of israels mossad intelligence agency and saying he will 
soon be replaced 
the courts decision tuesday widely reported in israeli 
newspapers marked the first time a court had ever overruled the 
military censors who have broad discretion over publication of news 
items in israel 
the disputed story in a weekly tel aviv newspaper hair did not 
give the name of the mossad head which is never made public 
it indicated the man was responsible for several of the mossads 
recent failures such as the discovery in west germany of false 
passports used by agents and events leading to the expulsion of 
agents from britain last year 
the report to be published in fridays edition of hair said 
the director will be replaced in a matter of days 
the director was the first to have risen from within the agencys 
ranks israel radio said there are two candidates likely to succeed 
him including one mossad official and one senior personality 
from outside the organization 
the new appointment must be approved by prime minister yitzhak 
shamir and finance minister shimon peres the heads of israels two 
main political blocs 
in overruling censorship on the story the supreme court said the 
press had a right to criticize public officials 
the court upheld censorship of any description of the mossad 
chief however citing the mans personal safety 
under israeli law military censors are empowered to ban 
publication of any news items deemed harmful to state security 
</TEXT>
