herald and review decatur ill on nuclear waste 
nuclear plants had a record year in 1988 they provided a full 20 
percent of the nations electricity but another report should 
give the rest of us pause 
in the same week the nonprofit research organization public 
citizen said 1987 was a dismal year for nuclear power industry 
in 1987 the private agency said there were at least 492 
violations of safety regulations at us nuclear power plants 
moreover there were nearly 3000 mishaps 430 emergency 
shutdowns and 104000 incidents in which workers were exposed to 
measurable doses of radiation 
the gravest problems facing mankind today involve pollution and 
the environment despite mandates from the federal government that 
every state establish hazardous waste sites and lowlevel nuclear 
waste storage sites no one wants such facilities in their back 
yard 
in the past we tended to assume we would solve the questions of 
what to do with radioactive waste and spent materials up the 
road now that road appears to be a dead end its possible 
theres no place on earth to put this stuff safely 
