<TEXT>
the chairman of the house armed services 
committee on wednesday proposed pooling money for such strategic 
weapons as star wars and the mx missile to force the incoming bush 
administration and congress to make tough spending decisions 
rep les aspin dwis said that under his 10year plan funds 
for the strategic defense initiative commonly known as star wars 
the trident mx and midgetman missiles and the b52 b1b and b2 
stealth bomber would be placed in a strategic pot 
the annual budget for the pot would remain constant at about 31 
billion the total budget for the strategic programs in 1989 with 
adjustments for inflation aspin said 
the 31 billion budget would be available for all strategic 
weapons with none of it earmarked for any specific weapon he said 
the program would force congress and the new administration to 
decide what specific weapon systems in the pot should be purchased 
and deployed and which should be delayed 
it allows you to make those kind of rational tradeoffs and then 
also to make the political tradeoffs aspin told a national press 
club audience the fact of the matter is youve got constituencies 
for these weapon systems and youve got to finally decide what 
youre going to do with them 
for example aspin mentioned continuing research and development 
funding for the truckmobile singlewarhead midgetman missile 
which many democrats in congress favor but the reagan administration 
proposed scrapping 
to compensate for moving forward on the midgetman aspin 
suggested slowing down stealth bomber purchases for two years and 
limiting spending on star wars to its current annual level of 4 
billion through 1996 
aspin also suggested retiring the poseidon ballistic missile 
submarines and the oldest b52s and using the money saved on 
operating costs for the two programs for earlier deployment of the 
railmobile version of the mx intercontinental ballistic missile 
the stealth bomber or star wars 
the committee chairman said the time has come for democrats and 
republicans white house and congress to put all the weapon systems 
into the pot take a long 10year view work the tradeoffs and 
build a strategic consensus 
