<TEXT>
former president jose luis bustamante credited 
with pioneering the 200mile limit at sea died wednesday at 93 the 
government said 
bustamante also was past president of the un international 
court of justice in the hague netherlands and was senatorforlife 
in the peruvian congress an honor bestowed on the nations 
democratically elected presidents on leaving office 
the government said bustamante died at military hospital of 
coronary complications resulting from deteriorating health over the 
past three years he had been hospitalized under intensive care 
since dec 10 
bustamante a politically independent lawyer became president in 
1945 and headed a centrist coalition government until 1948 when he 
was toppled in a military coup 
in 1947 bustamante decreed peruvian sovereignty extended for 200 
miles out to sea peruvian officials said the act set a precedent 
that has since been adopted by dozens of nations 
bustamante guided the world court from 1967 to 1970 he was also 
perus ambassador to uruguay and bolivia and in 1978 mediated a 
peaceful end to a border conflict between el salvador and honduras 
he is survived by a sister beatriz and a son jose luis a 
member of perus diplomatic corps 
</TEXT>
