this is the winter of the new england ski 
industrys discontent snowfall is below average and business is off 
despite efforts to blanket the slopes with manmade white stuff 
packed natural powder provides the best skiing conditions and 
most skiers tend to turn up their noses at the loose or frozen 
granular cover provided by snow guns if only for aesthetic reasons 
its a strange feeling to stand on a ski slope thats covered 
in white and look out around at the houses down below and its all 
covered in brown said phil camp director of the new england ski 
areas council the romance the ambiance just isnt there 
christopher h gill manager of great american ski renting cos 
store in north conway nh said the skiing is really good 
thanks to artificial snow making in his area but he said business 
is down about 25 percent from last year 
it really affects us when theres no snow down in boston 
gill said its funny if we get 3 inches of snow up here but 
theres a foot in boston it does us more good than the other way 
around 
camp who was hosting the councils annual convention for about 
500 ski resort operators at vermonts stratton mountain said 
